<task id="030" project="spaarke-matter-ui-enhancement-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Author Matter Health Composite chart definition (FR-DV-01)</title>
    <phase>3: Chart Definitions</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed>2026-05-27</completed>
    <estimated-hours>1-2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>060</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, chart-definition</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Dataverse record authoring (no React, no .cs). ADR-021 token vocabulary applied via the renderer; NFR-05 backward compat applies only at the renderer layer (task 020). No FULL-rigor quality gates required, but constraints must be cited and verified.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author a new `sprk_chartdefinition` Dataverse record named `Matter Health Composite` per FR-DV-01. Visual Type = `Donut` (100000004), Entity = `sprk_matter`. Provide the exact `sprk_optionsjson` payload below. Configure Drill Through to `sprk_kpiassessment` filtered by `_sprk_matter_value`. Verify the chart renders correctly on a Matter record with full KPI assessment data via a Visual Host instance bound to this chart def.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Dataverse configurator with familiarity with the Visual Host chart-definition contract and the `sprk_chartdefinition` schema. Comfortable using the Dataverse MCP (`create_record` / `read_query`) or PowerShell + Web API to author records.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A single `sprk_chartdefinition` record exists in Dataverse named `Matter Health Composite` with the exact `sprk_optionsjson` from FR-DV-01, Drill Through set to `sprk_kpiassessment` filtered by `_sprk_matter_value`. A test Visual Host instance bound to this chart def on a Matter record renders donut + 3 labeled breakdown rows + composite letter center + sub-value `XX/100` matching the Variant H prototype.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-DV-01 is the first chart definition added by this project and depends on the renderer changes shipped in task 020 (FR-VH-01: `donutLayout: "matrixRight"`, `donutCenterMode: "meanOfFields"`, field-pivot Donut consumption, `colorThresholds` segments). Per §6.4.0 (binding), the chart def must use ONLY existing visual types and the new generic Custom Options keys — no Matter-specific paths inside Visual Host. NFR-05 backward compatibility is the renderer's responsibility (verified in task 025); this task just authors the record and verifies render against the prototype.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>docs/architecture/VISUALHOST-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/VISUALHOST-SETUP-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/DonutChart.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/ChartRenderer.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-DV-01 — visual type Donut (100000004); entity sprk_matter; exact sprk_optionsjson payload</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">§6.4.0 (binding) — no new visual types; use only Donut + new generic Custom Options keys delivered by task 020</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-05 — existing chart defs unchanged (renderer-layer concern; verified in task 025)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens applied via the renderer (DonutChart) — token set names (brand/warning/danger) are renderer-resolved; chart def uses string keys only</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/VISUALHOST-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/VISUALHOST-SETUP-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-mcp-usage/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `docs/architecture/VISUALHOST-ARCHITECTURE.md` (per-visual-type Custom Options tables — confirm the new donut keys are documented; if not, flag dependency on FR-DOC-09 task) and `docs/guides/VISUALHOST-SETUP-GUIDE.md` (chart-def authoring examples).</step>
    <step order="2">Verify task 020 (DonutChart renderer extensions) has merged so `donutLayout`, `donutCenterMode`, `showBreakdownRows`, `breakdownValueFormat`, `fieldPivot` Donut consumption are all live. If not, BLOCK and report to user.</step>
    <step order="3">Author the `sprk_chartdefinition` record using mcp__dataverse__create_record (or PowerShell + Web API). Fields: `sprk_name` = "Matter Health Composite", `sprk_visualtype` = 100000004, `sprk_entityname` = "sprk_matter", `sprk_optionsjson` = exact JSON from `<notes>` below, drill-through entity = `sprk_kpiassessment`, drill-through filter field = `_sprk_matter_value`.</step>
    <step order="4">Verify the record was created by issuing `mcp__dataverse__read_query` for the new record id; confirm `sprk_optionsjson` round-trips identically.</step>
    <step order="5">Render verification: load a test Matter record (one with full KPI assessment data) in the dev environment; place a Visual Host instance bound to this chart def on a temporary form (or use the existing Performance pane scaffold if available); confirm it renders donut + 3 labeled rows + composite letter center + `XX/100` sub-value matching the Variant H prototype.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify Drill Through: click expand on the rendered card; confirm it opens the `sprk_kpiassessment` list filtered to the current matter.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 030 → ✅. Update current-task.md to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__create_record">Create the sprk_chartdefinition record</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">Verify round-trip of sprk_optionsjson</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__describe_table">Optional — confirm sprk_chartdefinition schema</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="dataverse-record">sprk_chartdefinition: "Matter Health Composite"</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-matter-ui-enhancement-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">A single active sprk_chartdefinition record named "Matter Health Composite" exists with sprk_visualtype = 100000004 and sprk_entityname = "sprk_matter".</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">sprk_optionsjson round-trips byte-identically to the payload in the notes block below.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Render verification (FR-DV-01 Acceptance): chart renders donut + 3 labeled rows + composite letter center + sub-value `XX/100`; expand opens KPI assessment list filtered to current matter.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md shows 030 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Exact sprk_optionsjson payload per spec FR-DV-01:

    ```json
    {
      "fieldPivot": {
        "fields": [
          { "field": "sprk_guidelinecompliancegrade_current", "label": "Guidelines Compliance" },
          { "field": "sprk_budgetcompliancegrade_current", "label": "Budget Controls" },
          { "field": "sprk_outcomecompliancegrade_current", "label": "Outcomes Success" }
        ]
      },
      "valueFormat": "letterGrade",
      "colorThresholds": [
        { "range": [0.85, 1.00], "tokenSet": "brand" },
        { "range": [0.70, 0.84], "tokenSet": "warning" },
        { "range": [0.00, 0.69], "tokenSet": "danger" }
      ],
      "donutLayout": "matrixRight",
      "donutCenterMode": "meanOfFields",
      "showBreakdownRows": true,
      "breakdownValueFormat": "scoreOver100"
    }
    ```

    Per Phase A.5 recon (spec.md §Assumptions), the rollups `sprk_guidelinecompliancegrade_current`, `sprk_budgetcompliancegrade_current`, `sprk_outcomecompliancegrade_current` already exist on `sprk_matter`. No schema change needed.
  </notes>

